      "span_text": "It is now the commonest cause of joint infection in knee replacement surgery 9,10 and a common cause of infection in knee arthroscopy.  There are cleaning recommendations available from tourniquet manufacturers which state that cuffs can be brushed with mild soap suds and rinsed with warm water."
